commText: Dhawan and Bairstow are at the crease. Dhawan is on strike. M Siddharth will open the attack
M Siddharth to Dhawan, no run, turning back in, Dhawan cuts to backward point
M Siddharth to Dhawan, no run, oh bit of away swing, Dhawan guides to short third man
Siddharth is mainly on to counter Jonny B. Oh dear, looks like the PBKS cheerleaders are slowly walking across the sightscreen without realising play has been paused by them
M Siddharth to Dhawan, no run, beaten! Again away swing from a fullish length, Dhawan looks to drive and misses
M Siddharth to Dhawan, no run, pushed to the off-side

M Siddharth to Dhawan, FOUR, sliced off the outer half of the bat! Fullish delivery swinging away, Dhawan looks to drive with an open bat face, was uppish but managed to split short third man and backward point
M Siddharth to Dhawan, 1 run, shortish delivery, rushed pull to deep mid-wicket
Naveen-ul-Haq, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhawan, no run, short of length delivery down leg, Dhawan looks to glance, ball rolls to short fine leg off the pad
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhawan, 1 run, leg-side offering again, flicked to deep square leg
Fine leg and deep backward square leg for Jonny B
Naveen-ul-Haq to Bairstow, 1 run, short of length angling in and cramping him for the pull, bounces more to hit Bairstow on the arm. Maybe glove, runs given
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhawan, 1 run, slower ball already, Dhawan mistimes the flick to backward square leg

Naveen-ul-Haq to Bairstow, FOUR, high quality shot! They have left off-side pretty open for Jonny B to hit against the incoming angle/movement from Naveen, Bairstow stands tall and punches it through cover-point
Deep point pushed back now

Naveen-ul-Haq to Bairstow, FOUR, but he offers a dolly full delivery outside off stump and Jonny B creams the cover drive in the gap and the deep point was never in play. Pressure releasing second half of the over from Naveen-ul-Haq
M Siddharth to Dhawan, 1 run, nudged to short mid-wicket. LSG will be happy with this single because they can have a crack at Jonny with left-arm spin now
Round the wicket of course

M Siddharth to Bairstow, 1 run, ohh almost chopped on and Jonny escapes strike immediately. Expectedly Siddharth darts the drifter that swings back in, Bairstow looks to slash through the off-side, ball just misses the stumps and goes to fine leg
M Siddharth to Dhawan, FOUR, smart from Dhawan. Shortish delivery, Dhawan moves across and pulls this over backward square leg knowing Siddharth is looking to cramp him for room
M Siddharth to Dhawan, FOUR, now gets the freebie full outside off stump, Dhawan leans forward and drives over cover for four more
M Siddharth to Dhawan, no run, slides down leg, Dhawan kind enough to glance it to short fine leg
M Siddharth to Dhawan, SIX, he's reverse-swept this for six over backward point. On the stumps, Dhawan puts on a bold face and smacks it high and handsome

This is a big box ticked by PBKS. LSG got Siddharth on for Bairstow but he's finished two overs and Jonny has faced only one ball. Will the home team still persist with the left-arm spinner to Bairstow next over should he continue to bat?
Mohsin Khan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Bairstow, no run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Bairstow defends
Mohsin Khan to Bairstow, SIX, muscled flat for six over deep backward square! Harmless short of a length delivery, Bairstow pulls and times it sweetly for a maximum
Mohsin Khan to Bairstow, no run, tries to repeat the shot, but this wasn't as short, hit on the thigh pad but ball pitched outside leg
Krunal, Pooran and Mohsin in a meeting at the top of the bowler's mark

Mohsin Khan to Bairstow, 1 run, oh direct-hit and Dhawan was gone! Bairstow defended this short of length delivery just beside the pitch. it was Dhawan's call for a quick single. Mohsin runs forward and underarms the ball towards the stumps, not a tough chance but he's missed the target. Bairstow escapes with a poor call for a run
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, no run, punched back to the bowler as Mohsin Khan bowls good length close to the off stump
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, no run, Dhawan cuts late but he finds backward point. Mohsin Khan has kind of pulled it back for LSG despite that six
Left-arm spinner out of the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Bairstow, 1 run, fullish and angling in, Bairstow pushes it to mid-off for a quick single
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhawan, no run, advances for a big hit, but Naveen-ul-Haq fires this wide and beats the bat
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhawan, 1 run, Dhawan slogs, drags this through backward square off the inside half of the bat
Naveen-ul-Haq to Bairstow, 1 run, slower delivery, Bairstow checks the flick to mid-wicket

Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhawan, 2 runs, ill-advised short slower delivery with fine leg in, Dhawan happily chips it over the infield but Bishnoi runs to the left from deep backward square leg to cut it off just inside the rope
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhawan, 1 run, short of length delivery, Dhawan toe-ends the cut to the off-side

Highlights (Overs 1-5) -> Sidhharth bowls an economical first over against Dhawan -> Bairstow hits back-to-back boundaries against Naveen -> 16 runs from Siddharth's next over, Dhawan belts him -> Bairstow hits a cracking six to greet Mohsin into the attack -> Punjab Kings off to an impressive start - 45/0 after 5 overs
Final PP over, PBKS will look to press harder and maximize. This could be LSG's chance too

Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, FOUR, oh great shot! Mohsin Khan saw Dhawan moving across for a leg-side hit and fired wide outside off stump, but Dhawan was still enough to stop the line early and change to a cut shot for a slap over point

Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, FOUR, oh he's just creamed the drive through the off-side! Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Dhawan plays the back foot drive with an angled bat face and it races away off the bat. Third man wasn't too far but he couldn't cut it off
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, no run, shortish and outside off stump, Dhawan toe-ends the slap it mid-off
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, SIX, back and across and smacked over mid-wicket. Slower delivery in the slot, Dhawan pulls it over mid-wicket for a maximum. He's taken 14 already off the over with two to go
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, 1 run, oh chips this short of length delivery towards mid-on. Looked like it stopped or jumped on the batter
Mohsin Khan to Bairstow, 1 run, short slower delivery, Bairstow looks to dab, under-edges it to point

Timeout. Perfect start for PBKS as they have managed a wicketless powerplay. LSG tried to use the left-arm spin matchup to Jonny Bairstow but the latter only faced one ball of that contest with Dhawan doing the bulk of the work. How are LSG going to approach now?
Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, no run, flatter delivery on off, Bairstow defends it watchfully
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, 1 run, slower through the air, close to the off-stump, Bairstow gets an inside edge past the leg-stump for a single
Krunal Pandya to Dhawan, 1 run, low slower through the air, worked through the on-side by Dhawan for a single
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, no run, darted at the stumps, Bairstow guides it back to Krunal
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, 1 run, on the shorter side, Bairstow punches it into the pocket at cover-point for one
Krunal Pandya to Dhawan, 1 run, drifting on the pads, Dhawan clips it through mid-wicket for a single. A wily start by Krunal Pandya, just four singles from his first over

Highest scores in the PP for Shikhar Dhawan (IPL) 48*(23) vs RR, Jaipur, 2019 42(29) vs MI, Mumbai WS, 2015 41*(21) vs MI, Visakhapatnam, 2012 41*(25) vs LSG, Lucknow, 2024 38*(23) vs CSK, Brabourne, 2010
Spin from both ends..
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, no run, full and quick on off, Dhawan drives it to the fielder at cover
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, 1 run, goes down on his knee and slogsweeps this to deep mid-wicket for a single does Dhawan
Ravi Bishnoi to Bairstow, 1 run, rocks back in the crease, Ravi Bishnoi follows him with a googly. Bairstow swivel pulls this to deep backward square leg for a single

Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, SIX, Dhawan brings up his fifty with a maximum! Tossed up delivery, right into the slot and Dhawan smokes it over deep mid-wicket for half-a-dozen. Has been a fantastic knock so far, just the kind of start PBKS expected of him
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, no run, quicker through the air outside off, Dhawan attempts a cut, connects thin air
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, no run, better comeback by Ravi Bishnoi, a quicker googly outside off, Dhawan gets beaten as he attempts a reverse sweep
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, SIX, Bairstow joins the act! Goes down on his knee and slogsweeps this over deep square leg for half-a-dozen. Runs coming thick and fast from both the ends
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, SIX, even bigger! A tossed up delivery, right into the slot and Bairstow clubs it over deep mid-wicket for an even bigger maximum. Back-to-back sixes!
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, 1 run, short and wide outside off, Bairstow cuts it through cover-point for a single
Krunal Pandya to Dhawan, no run, goes for the sweep, gets an inside edge on to the shoe does Dhawan
Krunal Pandya to Dhawan, 1 run, full toss on the pads, Dhawan flicks it through backward square leg for a single
Krunal Pandya to Bairstow, 1 run, short and wide outside off, Bairstow cuts it through backward point for a single
Mayank Yadav, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mayank Yadav to Bairstow, no run, 147.1kph, back of a length outside off, Bairstow makes room and tries to cut it away, gets beaten on the outside edge, didn't expect to be that quick I guess
Mayank Yadav to Bairstow, FOUR, 146.4kph, width on offer and Bairstow has carved this through point for a rollicking boundary. That absolutely raced away to the fence
Mayank Yadav to Bairstow, no run, 150.0kph. Fast, length delivery that beats Bairstow on the inside edge. This bloke can bowl quick
Mayank Yadav to Bairstow, 1 run, 141kph, back of a length outside off, Bairstow chops it into the off-side for a single

Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, FOUR, 148.6kph, short of a length on leg, Dhawan makes use of the pace and glances it past the fielder at short fine leg. Mayank Yadav is bowling quick, but the Punjab openers are playing him equally well
Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, 1 run, short of a length outside off, Dhawan steers it through backward point as Punjab Kings are 98/0 after 10 overs..

Over Summary (6-10 ov) * Mohsin Khan concedes 16 runs in the 6th over * Dhawan completes a 30-ball half-century with a huge six off Bishnoi * Krunal Pandya concedes 15 runs in the 9th over * Mayank Yadav hits 150 kmph in his maiden IPL over
Ravi Bishnoi [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, no run, on the shorter side, Dhawan cuts it to the fielder at point
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, 2 runs, 100-run stand up between the openers. Drifting on the pads and Dhawan works it through square leg for a couple of runs, good running between the wickets
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, 1 run, googly around off, Dhawan pushes it into the pocket at point for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Bairstow, no run, fired on off, Bairstow chops it to point
Ravi Bishnoi to Bairstow, no run, quicker through the air outside off, skids along the deck, Bairstow gets beaten as he attempts a late cut
Ravi Bishnoi to Bairstow, no run, another delivery quicker through the air, 104 clicks and Bairstow gets beaten on his cut again. Better over by Ravi Bishnoi
Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, no run, 155 clicks, he's bowling even quicker. Dhawan gets beaten as he tries to slash it away
Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, 1 run, 149kph, short and quick again, Dhawan goes for a pull, loses shape and gets a top edge that flies over the bowler
Mayank Yadav to Bairstow, no run, 141 kph, short and quick, some nice carry on leg, Bairstow goes for a cut, gets beaten due to the pace and bounce
Mayank Yadav to Bairstow, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mayank Yadav to Bairstow, out Caught by Stoinis!! Maiden IPL wicket for Mayank Yadav! Looks impressive. Goes short on middle and leg, Bairstow goes for a pull, but he miscues it towards deep mid-wicket. Stoinis charges in from the deep and completes a safe low catch to draw curtains to Bairstow's entertaining knpck. Just the breakthrough LSG were looking for. Will they claim a few more wickets and claw things back? Bairstow c Stoinis b Mayank Yadav 42(29) [4s-3 6s-3]
Out walks the impact player - Prabhsimran Singh.. He replaces Arshdeep Singh
Prabhsimran Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mayank Yadav to Prabhsimran, 1 run, 153kph, short of a length outside off, Prabhsimran chops it towards the off-side for a single

Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, FOUR, that's experience for you. Does it with nonchalance this time. Was a fast and short ball outside off, Dhawan makes use of all that pace and steers it away to the third man fence. The fielder was inside the circle and all Dhawan did was placed it past him

Highest partnerships vs LSG in the IPL (any wicket) 142 - Shubman Gill & Wridhhiman Saha (GT), Ahmedabad, 2023 115 - Faf du Plessis & Glenn Maxwell (RCB), Bengaluru, 2023 110 - Devon Conway & Ruturaj Gaikwad (CSK), Chennai, 2023 102 - Shikhar Dhawan & Jonny Bairstow (PBKS), Lucknow, 2024 96 - Faf du Plessis & Virat Kohli (RCB), Bengaluru, 2023
Ravi Bishnoi to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full and straight on off, Prabhsimran drives it through the off-side for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, 1 run, advances down the track and flicks this over mid-wicket for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Prabhsimran, FOUR, stand and deliver. Ravi Bishnoi goes full and Prabhsimran thumps it over the spinner's head for a rollicking boundary. Couldn't have placed it any better
Ravi Bishnoi to Prabhsimran, 1 run, sensible batting as Prabhsimran nudges this to long-on for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhawan, 1 run, googly on off, pushed into the pocket at cover-point by Dhawan for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Prabhsimran, SIX, that has gone the distance! A tossed up delivery by Ravi Bishnoi, right into the slot and Prabhsimran swings it over long-on, clears the fielder comfortably

Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, 1 run, 152kph, short of a length on middle and leg, Dhawan shuffles across and flicks it to fine leg for a single. Again it was travelling quickly, but straight to the fielder this time

Mayank Yadav to Prabhsimran, SIX, Prabhsimran playing a cameo! 149kph, short and quick on off, Prabhsimran slices it uppishly towards square third man. Mosin Khan in the deep takes the catch but he overhauls the boundary in the process
Mayank Yadav to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mayank Yadav to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Naveen-ul-Haq!! Mayank Yadav strikes again! Banged in short by him, Prabhsimran was hurried due to the pace as he went for a pull, and the top edge has been taken by Naveen at mid-on. Prabhsimran departs after playing a cameo. This contest is getting interesting. Mayank Yadav has brought the Lucknow Super Giants back into it. Prabhsimran c Naveen-ul-Haq b Mayank Yadav 19(7) [4s-1 6s-2]
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mayank Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, no run, oh smell the leather, says Mayank Yadav. 145kph, short and quick on off, Jitesh Sharma sways away
Mayank Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, no run, 144kph, banged in shorter by Mayank Yadav, Jitesh Sharma lets it through to the keeper
Mayank Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, 142 clicks, comparatively slower, Jitesh Sharma opens the bat face as the outside edge flies towards third man for one
Mohsin Khan [2.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Jitesh Sharma, FOUR, pitched up by the bowler on leg, Jitesh Sharma makes room and drills it right past the non-striker for a scintillating boundary
Mohsin Khan to Jitesh Sharma, no run, better delivery, yorker length ball at 139kph, Jitesh Sharma tries to squeeze it out, gets beaten on the outside edge
Mohsin Khan to Jitesh Sharma, wide, angled away from the batter outside off, Jitesh Sharma goes for a flashy drive, connects thin air, wide given
Mohsin Khan to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, short of a length outside off, Jitesh Sharma slices it through backward point for one
Dhawan reviews for a wide ball down the leg-side..
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, no run, not a wide, reckons the third umpire. Dhawan had moved across in the crease as he couldn't connect this short ball at the hips, onfield decision stays..
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, 1 run, on the shorter side, Dhawan hooks this over square leg for a single
Mohsin Khan to Jitesh Sharma, no run, fantastic over, just 7 runs from it. Was a slower one outside off, Jitesh Sharma swings early, connects thin air
Mayank Yadav to bowl his fourth and final over..

Over Summary (11-15 ov) -> PBKS bring up their 100 in the 11th over -> Bairstow miscues Mayank Yadav to deep mid-wicket, OUT for 42 -> Dhawan continues to find the boundaries -> Bishnoi concedes 14 runs in the 13th over -> Mayank bounces out Prabhsimran for a 7-ball 19
Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, 2 runs, 153.4kph, a low full toss outside off, Dhawan slices it through point for a brace, good stop in the deep by Bishnoi
Mayank Yadav to Dhawan, leg byes, 1 run, 153.9kph, fired on a fuller length on off, Dhawan gets an inside towards the keeper's left-side, takes a single
Mayank Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, no run, 148.6kph, short of a length outside off, Jitesh Sharma gets beaten as he attempts a cut
Mayank Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mayank Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Naveen-ul-Haq!! Banged in short and quick by Mayank Yadav, hurries the batter with ihs pace and bounce. Jitesh Sharma goes for a pull, gets a top edge towards mid-wicket and Naveen completes a good running catch. Slides in front of him and completes the formalities as Jitesh walks back after playing a rusty knock. Couldn't get going against the pacer at all. Jitesh Sharma c Naveen-ul-Haq b Mayank Yadav 6(9) [4s-1]

Strategic timeout! Match poised on an interesting note as Punjab Kings need 61 runs in 26 balls. Mayank Yadav has single-handedly turned this match on its head. Can LSG manage to contain the opposition batters towards the final overs? Let's find out..
Liam Livingstone, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mayank Yadav to Livingstone, no run, even Livingstone can't spot the ball. Reads it very late. This was fired at 151.8kph, right into the slot, Livingstone swings and misses
Mayank Yadav to Livingstone, 1 run, end of a brilliant spell by the 21 year old pacer. 148kph, length delivery as Livingstone heaves it across the line, gets a single through mid-wicket

Mohsin Khan to Livingstone, 1 run, width on offer and Livingstone slashes it to deep point where Bishnoi puts in a dive to stop it. Livingstone struggling with that injury while running between the wickets, just gets a single
Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohsin Khan to Dhawan, out Caught by de Kock!! Dhawan departs after playing a fine knock. Was a short ball down the leg-side, Dhawan goes for a pull and gloves it to the keeper. de Kock puts in a forward dive and completes a good catch. Wickets falling in a cluster as the Giants are on top. Dhawan c de Kock b Mohsin Khan 70(50) [4s-7 6s-3]
Sam Curran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohsin Khan to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohsin Khan to Sam Curran, out Caught by Pooran!! Two wickets in two balls for Mohsin Khan. He's on a hat-trick. Goes short and quick, Sam Curran goes for a pull, loses his shape and gets a top-edge towards mid-on. Pooran settles under the skier and pouches it safely. That's a duck for Sam Curran as LSG continue to dominate the second half of the run chase.. Sam Curran c Pooran b Mohsin Khan 0(1)
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohsin Khan to Shashank Singh, 1 run, Shashank Singh facing the hat-trick ball, plays it watchfully, knocking it towards the off-side for a single
Mohsin Khan to Livingstone, 1 run, pulls the short ball through mid-wicket, just a single

Mohsin Khan to Shashank Singh, 1 run, run-out chance missed. Shashank Singh knocks it to point and calls for a single, Stoinis had plenty of time to score a direct-hit at the keeper's end with Livingstone limping, but he misses
Naveen-ul-Haq [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shashank Singh, FOUR, on the shorter side, Shashank Singh pulls it towards the left of deep mid-wicket and manages to beat Bishnoi's dive near the boundary
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shashank Singh, 1 run, banged in short by Naveen-ul-Haq, Shashank Singh goes for a pull, gets a top edge towards third man for one
Mohsin Khan is off the field, looks like he's struggling with cramps, lying on the floor beyond the boundary..
Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, 1 run, heaves this length ball through the leg-side for a single
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shashank Singh, leg byes, 1 run, full and quick on leg, off the pads the ball rolls towards the on-side
Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, no run, slower delivery outside off, Livingstone swings and misses, played that way too early
Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, 1 run, swings this through the on-side for a single does Livingstone
Equation: 48 runs required in 12 balls..
Krunal Pandya [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Livingstone, no run, fired outside off, Livingstone leaves it alone, just inside the tramline
A few changes in the field, short fine leg moves to cover
Krunal Pandya to Livingstone, 1 run, a lot slower through the air, Livingstone moves across and scoops this to short fine leg for one
Krunal Pandya to Shashank Singh, 1 run, yorker length ball outside off, Shashank Singh squeezes it into the off-side for one
Krunal Pandya to Livingstone, no run, short and quick outside off, Livingstone gets beaten outside off
Krunal Pandya to Livingstone, FOUR, stands tall and thumps this over mid-off. Finally connects one does Livingstone, but too late now.. They need 42 runs in 7 balls
Krunal Pandya to Livingstone, 1 run, full and wide outside off, Livingstone thumps it over covers for a single

Dead ball! Was a short ball and Livingstone pulls it powerfully towards mid-wicket. The ball hits the spidercam, else it was a six. That kind of an evening for Livingstone. Nothing going right for him
Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, wide, short and slow on off, Livingstone goes for a pull, gets beaten though
Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, SIX, on a length around middle and leg, Livingstone swings it over deep square leg for half-a-dozen. Equation - 34 off 5

Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, FOUR, almost goes the distance. Pitched up by Naveen-ul-Haq outside off, Livingstone lunges forward and bludgeons it towards deep extra cover as the ball lands in front of the cushions. For a moment it looked like a flat six, but wasn't to be

Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, SIX, short and punished! Picks the length early, stands tall and spanks it right over the bowler's head for six more. He's dealing in boundaries. Can't run quickly, but he's striking them big
Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, no run, on the shorter side, slower too, Livingstone has a swing and a miss
Naveen-ul-Haq to Livingstone, 1 run, on a length around off, slower delivery as Livingstone heaves it to deep mid-wicket on the bounce
Naveen-ul-Haq to Shashank Singh, 1 run, LSG beat PBKS by 21 runs! A short ball outside off and Shashank Singh slaps it through cover to draw curtains to the game..

23:21 Local Time, 17:51 GMT, 23:21 IST: Lucknow Super Giants register their first win of the season and get off the mark in the points table. LSG went into the innings break having scored 199/8 in 20 overs. However, Shikhar Dhawan and Jonny Bairstow came out all guns blazing and dominated the powerplay. Both the openers attacked the bowlers from the outset and had a fantastic opening partnership of 102. Just when the run chase looked in Punjab's control, young pacer - Mayank Yadav came into the attack and bowled an inspiring spell. He hit the 150-kph mark regularly and rattled the Punjab batters with his raw pace and bounce. He broke the opening partnership by dismissing Bairstow initially, and later got two more wickets in the form of Prabhsimran Singh and Jitesh Sharma. Shikhar Dhawan who was watching wickets fall from the other end, lost momentum and even he succumbed under pressure. Punjab kept losing wickets at regular intervals for the rest of the chase and despite Livingstone's cameo, they fell short by 21 runs. Stay around for the presentations..

Shikhar Dhawan | PBKS captain: They played well, pity that Livi (Livingstone) got injured, that hurt us, he would have come at 4. We started off well, but Mayank bowled well with his pace. It was nice facing him, I was surprised at his pace, but I wanted to use his pace against him, but he bowled the bouncers and the yorkers well. I was quite mindful, asked the batters to use the short side and use his pace, but he bowled into his body (on Bairstow's dismissal) and got him OUT, I said the same to Jitesh as well. But Mohsin bowled really well, he kept a good length and suffocated us. We will have to analyse these defeats, the drop catch did cost us some momentum. That's something we'll have to improve going forward.

Morne Morkel | LSG bowling coach: Very happy with the win, first point on the board, it's a nice feeling. Bowlers took it on a good wicket. They had a good start but the bowlers were brilliant to stay in the game. Young Mayank Yadav bowled with serious heat and got wickets. Very happy for him. He got injured in the first warm up game last season and got ruled out so had to manage him better this time. He bowled 155 tonight and made life uncomfortable. He ran in and that was the pleasing thing for all of us. It was a good wicket and for him to stick to that hard length - that's his strength - in this humidity in your first game in front of a big crowd, credit to him. Happy with 2 points tonight.

PBKS run-chase Overs 1-10: 98/0 (RR: 9.8) Overs 11-19: 61/5 (RR: 6.77) Last over: 19 runs PBKS’ s 178/5 is the highest total in a run-chase in 38 T20s played in Lucknow. Dhawan’s innings progression First 10 balls: 8 runs (SR: 80) Next 25 balls: 47 runs (SR: 188) Last 15 balls: 15 runs (SR: 100) LSG’s record while batting first in the IPL Matches: 16 Won: 13 Lost: 2 NR: 1 Most 50-plus scores in a losing cause in the IPL 28 - Virat Kohli 25 - David Warner 19 - Shikhar Dhawan 18 - KL Rahul

Nicholas Pooran | LSG captain: Wonderful start, nice to win in front of the home crowd. We had conversations, spoke about getting good starts. Spoke about getting the right combinations. It was a good total. It's a big venue, one side is big, one side short. It's about getting wickets and getting boundaries. It's only going to get challenging. Shikhar and Bairstow played well. They didn't take the game away from us as we got wickets at the right time. Mayank's was the story of the night.That was an inspiring performance, he (Mayank) is a young guy. He showed the entire world how good he is. He is not only fast, but also is accurate. It's the beauty of the IPL, gives the local players to perform. Wonderful platform. Every game is an opportunity, expect them to get better with every game. The groundsmen have contributed, as a batsman you can't ask for anything more.

Mayank Yadav | Player of the Match: Never thought it would be such a good debut. Was nervous before the match. Tried to stick to my pace and aim at the stumps. Was thinking about using slower ones initially, but stuck to the quick ones. First wicket (Bairstow) was special. It's good to debut at such a young age. Had a few goals, but can't help if injuries come in the way..

So after a rare win by an away team last night, we are back to home teams winning. Lucknow got off the mark with an impressive win, and now - Delhi Capitals and Mumbai Indians are the only two teams to open their account. Both the bottom placed teams have lost two games each. We'll be back with a double-header tomorrow as Gujarat Titans lock horns with Sunrisers Hyderabad and Delhi Capitals take on the Chennai Super Kings later in the day. Do join us. For now, it's a goodbye from our side. Goodnight!
